  "text": "Horizontal gene transfer (HGT) has distributed genes that are required for pathogenicity among many bacterial lineages [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] . HGT, also known as lateral gene transfer, occurs when genes move between different genomes.",
